09/09/2004
TIRANA, Albania -- Prime Minister Fatos Nano met with visiting Kosovo President Ibrahim Rugova on Wednesday (8 September). 
At a joint news conference afterwards, they pledged to find ways to strengthen co-operation on border security, the free movement of citizens, and economic activities. 
Rugova, who also met with Albanian President Alfred Moisiu, reiterated that the 23 October parliamentary elections in Kosovo would be peaceful, free and democratic.
Also Wednesday, EBRD President Jean Lemierre started a three-day visit to Albania. 
The focus of the trip is on aid for development projects. 
The EBRD has so far lent 210m euros to 17 such projects. 
(Albanian News - 09/09/04; ATA, EBRD press release - 08/09/04)
